The paper deals with the computation of spanning trees in the semi-streaming model, which is a variant of the streaming model frequently used for the computation of graph problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The study of graph problems and algorithms for them could also fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of randomized algorithms and probability theory could indicate that the paper belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
